#include<iostream>
using namespace std;

struct Point{
    int x;
    int y;
};

struct Rect{
    Point c1;
    Point c2;
};

int main(){
    int T;
    Rect r1, r2, r3;
    scanf("%d", &T);

    while(T--){
        scanf("%d %d %d %d", &r1.c1.x, &r1.c1.y, &r1.c2.x, &r1.c2.y);
        scanf("%d %d %d %d", &r2.c1.x, &r2.c1.y, &r2.c2.x, &r2.c2.y);

        if(r2.c1.x >= r1.c1.x && r2.c1.x < r1.c2.x){
            r3.c1.x = r2.c1.x;
            r3.c2.x = r1.c2.x;
        }
        else if(r2.c2.x > r1.c1.x && r2.c2.x <= r1.c2.x){
            r3.c1.x = r1.c1.x;
            r3.c2.x = r2.c2.x;
        }
        else{
            r3.c1.x = r3.c2.x = 0;
        }

        if(r2.c1.y >= r1.c1.y && r2.c1.y < r1.c2.y){
            r3.c1.y = r2.c1.y;
            r3.c2.y = r1.c2.y;
        }
        else if(r2.c2.y > r1.c1.y && r2.c2.y <= r1.c2.y){
            r3.c1.y = r1.c1.y;
            r3.c2.y = r2.c2.y;
        }
        else{
            r3.c1.y = r3.c2.y = 0;
        }

        if((r3.c2.x-r3.c1.x) > 0 && (r3.c2.y - r3.c1.y) > 0){
            printf("%d %d %d %d\n", r3.c1.x, r3.c1.y, r3.c2.x, r3.c2.y);
        }
        else{
            printf("No Overlap\n");
        }
    }
}
